20up%20totalitarian%20regimes%20by%20making%20a%20mockery%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Constitutions%20in%20some%20of%20the%20Afro-Asian%20countries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Furban-elitist-views-centre-files-affidavit-in-sc-opposing-same-sex-marriages%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegation%20of%20elitism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20specifically%20%E2%80%9Curban%20elitism%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20made%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20demand%20of%20same-sex%20marriage%20in%20an%20ongoing%20case%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20A%20similar%20allegation%20was%20made%20not%20long%20ago%20in%20the%20case%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findias-poor-must-right-privacy%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eright%20to%20privacy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Although%20the%20court%20brushed%20aside%20this%20argument%20in%20both%20the%20cases%2C%20it%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fright-to-privacy-supreme-court-2%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elikely%20to%20be%20invoked%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20future%20rights-based%20litigation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20appears%20compelling%20and%20has%20a%20strong%20appeal.%20The%20argument%20delegitimises%20a%20demand%20by%20indicating%20it%20to%20be%20a%20whim%20of%20privileged%20few.%20It%20raises%20the%20question%2C%20should%20the%20legislature%2Fcourts%20discuss%20such%20issues%20at%20all%20or%20is%20it%20a%20waste%20of%20time%3F%20Therefore%2C%20this%20argument%20of%20%E2%80%98urban%20elitism%E2%80%99%20deserves%20critical%20scrutiny.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20demand%20categorised%20as%20%E2%80%98elitist%E2%80%99%20implies%20that%20it%20comes%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98few%20privileged%E2%80%99%20sections.%20It%20is%20also%20deemed%20unnecessary%20by%20the%20larger%20lesser%20privileged%20sections%20who%20are%20burdened%20with%20the%20real%20issues%20of%20life.%20To%20suggest%20that%20a%20demand%20is%20%E2%80%9Curban%E2%80%9D%20implies%20that%20it%20is%20relevant%20to%20people%20in%20urban%20settings%20and%20irrelevant%20outside.%20The%20opposition%20to%20a%20supposed%20%E2%80%98urban%20elitist%E2%80%99%20demand%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20perceived%20irrelevance%20of%20such%20demands%20to%20human%20life.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2F53-of-adults-in-india-support-legalisation-of-same-sex-marriages-finds-pew-research-center%5C%22%3E53%25%20of%20Adults%20in%20India%20Support%20Legalisation%20of%20Same-Sex%20Marriages%2C%20Finds%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20same-sex%20marriage%2C%20the%20argument%20of%20urban%20elitism%20gets%20frequently%20buttressed%20with%20visuals%20of%20people%20in%20burlesque%20costumes%20in%20urban%20settings.%20These%20visuals%20and%20arguments%20do%20not%20objectively%20explain%20the%20phenomena%20or%20further%20social%20or%20legal%20discourse.%20Instead%20they%20trivialise%20it%20and%20tend%20to%20arouse%20disdain%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98othering%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EModern%20science%20empirically%20recognises%20homosexuality%20as%20a%20naturally%20occurring%20phenomena%20across%20demographics%2C%20countries%20and%20cultures.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20operated%20on%20this%20understanding%20while%20deciding%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENavtej%20Jauhar%20v%20Union%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhere%20consensual%20sex%20among%20homosexuals%20was%20decriminalised%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESociologically%20urban%20spaces%20have%20always%20provided%20a%20sense%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ffuture%2Farticle%2F20170529-the-reasons-you-can-never-be-anonymous-again%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epersonal%20safety%20in%20anonymity%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Large%20cities%20also%20give%20a%20sense%20of%20inclusion%20by%20sustaining%20small%20but%20sizable%20communities%20in%20otherwise%20diverse%20populations.%20Therefore%2C%20what%20seems%20like%20an%20%E2%80%9Curban%E2%80%9D%20demand%20is%20largely%20attributable%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20safety%20that%20facilitates%20expression%20of%20desire%20without%20fear%20of%20physical%20hurt%20or%20social%20ostracisation.%20It%20is%20not%20an%20urban%20demand%20but%20is%20often%20expressed%20freely%20in%20urban%20areas.%20The%20desire%20to%20marry%20exists%20irrespective%20of%20urban%20spaces%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20is%20not%20urban%20by%20nature.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20apparent%20occurrence%20of%20this%20demand%20in%20urban%20spaces%20is%20purely%20situational%20and%20not%20a%20causative%20factor%20for%20homosexuality%20or%20the%20desire%20to%20marry.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20the%20desire%20to%20get%20married%20are%20not%20a%20function%20of%20wealth.%20It%20is%20another%20matter%20that%20the%20rich%20can%20afford%20to%20contest%20causes%20before%20the%20courts.%20They%20can%20take%20refuge%20in%20their%20private%20spaces%20and%20enjoy%20amenities.%20They%20can%20perhaps%20live%20with%20lesser%20social%20capital%20compared%20to%20those%20without%20financial%20security.%20People%20with%20resources%20are%20obviously%20able%20to%20raise%20their%20demand%20without%20fear%20of%20consequences%20that%20may%20become%20incumbent%20on%20the%20lesser%20privileged.%20Thus%2C%20creating%20the%20illusion%20that%20this%20demand%20comes%20from%20those%20who%20are%20rich.%20But%20it%20is%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20false%20correlation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EListen%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flgbtqia%2Fmarriage-equality-onir-podcast%5C%22%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20Exhausting%20to%20See%20the%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Aggression%20in%20the%20Same-Sex%20Marriage%20Case%3A%20Onir%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20contention%20was%20that%20only%20a%20few%20elites%20were%20concerned%20and%20their%20concerns%20were%20not%20shared%20by%20the%20majority.%20The%20court%20reasoned%20that%20such%20assertion%20was%20based%20on%20misunderstanding%20of%20the%20constitutional%20position.%20Our%20Constitution%20places%20the%20individual%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20its%20focus%2C%20guaranteeing%20civil%20and%20political%20rights%20in%20the%20Part%20III%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20begs%20another%20question.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20assume%20that%20a%20demand%20comes%20from%20a%20privileged%20few%20residing%20in%20urban%20spaces%20or%20any%20other%20cultural%2C%20linguistic%20or%20ethnic%20minority%20group.%20Should%20it%20be%20rejected%20merely%20because%20the%20people%20demanding%20it%20are%20fewer%20in%20number%20and%20others%20do%20not%20share%20their%20concern%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20larger%20numbers%20create%20political%20outcomes%2C%20the%20law%20always%20protects%20the%20individual%20and%20minority%20so%20that%20they%20can%20have%20an%20equal%20participation%20in%20society.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20legality%20of%20demands%20cannot%20be%20assessed%20in%20terms%20of%20numerical%20strength%20but%20within%20the%20confines%20of%20legal%20principles.%20Numbers%20are%20relevant%20in%20assessing%20political%20support.%20Characterisation%20of%20a%20demand%20as%20urban%20elitist%20often%20places%20reliance%20on%20political%20support%20than%20legal%20merit%20of%20that%20demand.%20In%20a%20democracy%20committed%20to%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20such%20logic%20has%20never%20found%20favour%20with%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EArjun%20Harkauli%20and%20Adit