contract%20was%20terminated%20last%20October%20following%20the%20rapper's%20controversial%20remarks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20had%20originally%20planned%20to%20write%20off%20all%20existing%20Yeezy%20stock%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20%24500%20million%2C%20before%20shareholder%20pressure%20reversed%20this%20decision%20in%20May.%20Instead%2C%20the%20clothing%20brand%20has%20pledged%20to%20donate%20some%20of%20the%20profits%20from%20the%20sale%20to%20causes%20fighting%20antisemitism%20and%20racism%2C%20but%20the%20total%20contribution%20to%20charitable%20causes%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20confirmed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20Ye%20%E2%80%93%20who%20is%20reported%20by%20the%20FT%20to%20have%20generated%20%E2%82%AC1.7%20billion%20in%20sales%20and%20almost%20%E2%82%AC700%20million%20in%20operating%20profit%20for%20the%20company%20%E2%80%93%20Adidas%20may%20report%20its%20first%20operating%20loss%20in%2031%20years%2C%20but%20the%20sale%20of%20Yeezy%20inventory%20will%20likely%20ease%20these%20woes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sportswear%20maker%20is%20also%20embroiled%20in%20a%20legal%20dispute%20with%20Ye%2C%20after%20accusing%20him%20of%20%26quot%3Bmishandling%20virtually%20all%20of%20the%20marketing%20funds%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20Yeezy%20project.%20West%20admitted%20on%20the%20Nick%20Cannon%20podcast%20to%20spending%20%2450%20million%20on%20his%20%26quot%3BSunday%20Service%26quot%3B%20gospel%20choir%20tour%20%E2%80%93%20though%20whether%20this%20was%20Adidas%20money%2C%20he%20didn't%20clarify.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Yeezys%2C%20they%20were%20selling%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20instead%20of%20paying%20for%20ads%2C%20I%20invested%20it%20in%20the%20church.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fye-yeezy-shoes-trainers-sportswear-adidas-sale-kanye-west-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690