hed%20to%20build%202.5%20metres%20of%20the%20road.%20Locals%20say%20that%20they%20are%20unsure%20of%20what%20will%20become%20of%20the%20structure%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20minaret%20and%20the%20pillar%20that%20supports%20it%20and%20the%20mosque.%20In%20multiple%20pleas%20to%20the%20administration%2C%20the%20Wakf%20secretary%20has%20requested%20the%20District%20Magistrate%20to%20not%20demolish%20the%20mosque.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThirty%20temples%20on%20the%20path%20have%20been%20affected%20as%20well%2C%20say%20administration.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CAll%20religious%20structures%20are%20treated%20equally%2C%20and%20we%20have%20demolished%20everything%20within%20the%20specified%20width%20of%20the%20Rampath.%20Approximately%2030%20temples%20have%20also%20been%20demolished%2C%20and%20their%20idols%20were%20respectfully%20taken%20to%20other%20temples%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amit%20Singh%2C%20the%20additional%20district%20magistrate%20of%20Ayodhya%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20treat%20a%20200-year-old%20mosque%20as%20an%20exception%20then%20someone%20can%20use%20the%20same%20for%20their%20house.%20You%20will%20see%20that%20nine%20metres%20of%20a%20famous%20temple%20in%20Hanuman%20Garhi%20is%20also%20marked%20for%20demolition%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20589px)%2085vw%2C%20589px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152854%2F1-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22589%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152854%2F1-1.jpeg%20512w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152854%2F1-1-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664752%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20minaret%20of%20Khajur%20ki%20Masjid%20in%20the%20background%20is%20to%20be%20demolished%20for%20the%20widening%20of%20the%20Rampath.%20Photo%3A%20Vipul%20Kumar%20and%20Alishan%20Jafri%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Nitin%20Mishra%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Ayodhya%20who%20practices%20at%20the%20Lucknow%20bench%20of%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%2C%20the%20demolition%20drive%20comes%20very%20close%20to%20entirely%20destroying%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20heritage.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20many%20old%20temples%20on%20the%20pathway%20and%20many%20of%20them%20have%20been%20partly%20demolished%20too.%20They%20have%20their%20own%20customs%20and%20people%20are%20attached%20to%20their%20temples.%20The%20entire%20exercise%20could%20have%20been%20avoided.%20It%20is%20a%20diverse%20city%20and%20that%20diversity%20is%20being%20replaced%20entirely%2C%E2%80%9D%20Mishra%20says.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20384px)%2085vw%2C%20384px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152908%2F3-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152908%2F3-1.jpeg%20384w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152908%2F3-1-225x300.jpeg%20225w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664754%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20partly%20demolished%20house%20on%20the%20under%20construction%20Rampath.%20Photo%3A%20Vipul%20Kumar%20and%20Alishan%20Jafri%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20also%20the%20question%20of%20what%20becomes%20of%20the%20city%20after%20these%20changes.%20Residents%20say%20that%20so%20far%20Ayodhya%20was%20the%20poor%20man%E2%80%99s%20pilgrimage%20site%20but%20the%20new%20changes%20would%20alter%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20culture%20and%20its%20relationship%20with%20locals.%20Professor%20Raghuvansh%20Mani%20Tripathi%20who%20teaches%20English%20at%20the%20Siddharth%20University%20and%20whose%20house%20was%20partly%20demolished%20during%20the%20Rampath%20road%20widening%20drive%2C%20feels%20that%20Ayodhya%20is%20on%20its%20way%20towards%20becoming%20a%20commercial%20city.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20bird%E2%80%99s%20eye%20view%20of%20the%20path%20leaves%20you%20with%20the%20impression%20of%20a%20lightning%20bolt%20having%20sliced%20through%20several%20buildings%2C%20including%20houses%2C%20shops%2C%20and%20shrines%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20road.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20city%20and%20a%20temple%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20stated%20goals%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20party%20and%20its%20ideological%20parent%2C%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh.%20The%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%20temple%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20inaugurated%20in%20January%20next%20year%2C%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20government%20has%20already%20hailed%20it%20as%20one%20of%20its%20top%20achievements%20in%20the%20past%20decade.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20in%20Ayodhya%20many%20residents%20are%20struggling%20to%20identify%20with%20this%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20Ayodhya.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EColumnist%20K.P.%20Singh%2C%20for%20one%2C%20sees%20the%20recent%20spate%20of%20changes%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20radically%20metamorphosise%20the%20Ganga-Jamuni%20syncretic%20culture%20that%20represented%20Ayodhya%20into%20an%20exclusively%20Hindu%20city.%20Singh%20feels%20that%20the%20diversity%20of%20Ayodhya%20is%20being%20destroyed%20by%20the%20drive%20that%20has%20shown%20scant%20regard%20for%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20own%20heritage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20BJP%20does%20not%20fear%20turning%20the%20anger%20of%20Ayodhya%20residents%20into%20their%20loss%20in%20the%202024%20general%20elections.%20They%20want%20to%20benefit%20from%20projecting%20Ayodhya%20as%20the%20model%20ideological%20city%20on%20a%20national%20level%20before%20the%202024%20elections%2C%20no%20matter%20what%20backlash%20they%20face%20in%20Ayodhya%20itself%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Singh.%20He%20suspects%20that%20for%20electoral%20mobilisation%2C%20the%20BJP%20could%20well%20issue%20a%20call%20of%20%E2%80%98Ayodhya%20%3Cem%3Echalo%20%3C%2Fem%3E(come%20to%20Ayodhya).%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20initial%20proposal%20was%20to%20create%20a%2024-metre-wide%20and%2013-kilometre-long%20Rampath.%20After%20protests%20by%20locals%2C%20the%20width%20was%20reduced%20to%2020%20metres%20since%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20old%20city%20had%20very%20narrow%20and%20busy%20streets%20with%20sprawling%20markets%20and%20densely%20inhabited%20neighbourhoods.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20this%20road%20being%20constructed%20when%20there%20are%20other%20options%20available%2C%E2%80%9D%20asked%20Nandu%20Gupta%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20Trade%20Union%20in%20Ayodhya.%20According%20to%20Gupta%2C%20to%20prevent%20this%20chaos%2C%20the%20best%20option%20available%20was%20the%20route%20from%20behind%20the%20Janmabhoomi%20to%20Faizabad.%20A%20total%20of%204%2C500%20shops%20and%202%2C000%20families%20have%20been%20affected%20by%20the%20four%20road%20projects%2C%20namely%20Rampath%2C%20Bhakti%20Path%2C%20Janmabhoomi%20Path%2C%20and%20Dharmpath.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fas-ram-mandir-nears-completion-ayodhyas-traders-bear-hidden-costs%5C%22%3EAs%20Ram%20Mandir%20Nears%20Completion%2C%20Ayodhya%E2%80%99s%20Traders%20Bear%20Hidden%20Costs%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CApproximately%202%2C000%20of%20these%20shops%20have%20been%20completely%20demolished%2C%20with%20promises%20made%20to%20provide%20shops%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20Ayodhya.%20However%2C%20not%20more%20than%20400%20shops%20are%20being%20provided%20at%20a%20rate%20of%20Rs%209%2C500%20per%20square%20meter.%20This%20means%20that%20a%20shopkeeper%20will%20need%20to%20spend%20Rs%2015%20lakh%20for%20a%20shop%20in%20a%20good%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gupta%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20a%20slightly%20different%20version.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EADM%20Singh%20said%20that%20around%20Rs%20100%20crores%20have%20been%20allotted%20by%20the%20government%20for%20the%20compensation%20of%20land%20and%20buildings%2C%20including%202%2C200%20shops%2C%20800%20houses%2C%2030%20temples%2C%20nine%20mosques%2C%20and%20six%20mazars%20that%20fall%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Rampath.%20%E2%80%9CCurrently%2C%20285%20shops%20have%20been%20completely%20demolished%2C%20and%20more%20than%20350%20shops%20will%20be%20allotted%20to%20the%20owners%20of%20fully%20demolished%20shops%20on%20lease%20for%2030%20years%2C%20which%20will%20cost%20them%20around%20Rs%2010%20lakhs%20for%20each%20shop%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152915%2F4-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22616%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152915%2F4-1.jpeg%20512w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24152915%2F4-1-300x225.jpeg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-664755%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20old%20structure%20at%20Faizabad.%20Photo%3A%20Vipul%20Kumar%20and%20Alishan%20Jafri%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMahendra%2C%20who%20practices%20homeopathy%20and%20whose%20rented%20chambers%20have%20been%20reduced%20to%20less%20than%20half%20of%20its%20original%20size%20complained%20about%20the%20loss%20of%20business%20on%20the%20route.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20compensation%20will%20be%20provided%20to%20the%20landlords%2C%20and%20not%20to%20the%20tenants%20operating%20their%20business%20from%20the%20shops.%20Renting%20spaces%20in%20other%20locations%20is%20expensive%2C%20he%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20shops%20that%20are%20being%20allocated%20by%20the%20development%20authority%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20ones%20being%20demolished%20for%20the%20Rampath%20project%20are%20very%20costly%2C%20and%20only%20big%20businessmen%20can%20afford%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELocal%20businesses%20on%20the%2013-kilometre%20route%20of%20the%20Rampath%20have%20suffered%20too.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20January%20of%20this%20year%2C%20the%20partial%20demolition%20of%20my%20house%20meant%20that%20I%20lost%20my%20beauty%20parlour%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20lost%20the%20general%20store%20he%20used%20to%20run.%20My%20husband%20is%20now%20operating%20the%20store%20in%20a%20small%20space%20in%20front%20of%20the%20house.%20I%20received%20Rs%201%2C60%2C000%20as%20compensation%20for%20the%20building%2C%20but%20it%20would%20cost%20me%20around%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20to%20make%20it%20liveable%20after%20the%20demolition%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Neelam%20Maurya.%20Maurya%E2%80%99s%20beauty%20parlour%20is%20now%20shut.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fayodhya-mosque-babri-masjid-ram-temple-title-supreme-court%5C%22%3EConstruction%20on%20the%20Ayodhya%20Mosque%20Is%20Yet%20to%20Begin.%20Here%20Is%20Why%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELegal%20loopholes%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENitin%20Mishra%20also%20claimed%20that%20there%20are%20legal%20loopholes%20in%20the%20entire%20exercise.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20been%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Land%20Acquisition%20Act%20of%202013%20have%20not%20been%20applied.%20Instead%2C%20the%20government%20has%20used%20a%20sale%20and%20purchase%20model%2C%20passed%20through%20an%20ordinance%2C%20to%20buy%20the%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20by%20the%20time%20an%20individual%20can%20approach%20the%20court%2C%20bulldozers%20will%20have%20reached%20her%20building.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20the%20people%20in%20these%20areas%20are%20tenants%2C%20he%20added%2C%20implying%20that%20few%20would%20want%20to%20open%20a%20chapter%20of%20conflict%20with%20the%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Intezar%20Hussain%20who%20is%20representing%20the%20Khajur%20ki%20Masjid%20Waqf%20reiterated%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20point%20on%20the%20legal%20aspects%20having%20been%20neglected.%20There%20was%20no%20invitation%20of%20objections%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIntezar%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20compensation%20is%20based%20on%20the%20circle%20rate%20(land%20price%20fixed%20by%20the%20government)%20of%202017%2C%20which%20is%20significantly%20lower%20than%20the%20rate%20in%202023.%20On%20March%201%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Wakf%20Committee%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20in%20the%20high%20court%20to%20move%20the%20road%20by%202.5%20metres%20to%20the%20opposite%20side%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20ensuring%20the%20preservation%20of%20the%20mosque%E2%80%99s%20minaret.%20The%20land%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20also%20belongs%20to%20the%20Shia%20Waqf%20Board%2C%20Hussain%20claimed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20advocate%20said%2C%20the%20P%3Cspan%3Elaces%20of%20Worship%20Act%20is%20being%20violated%20in%20the%20process%20of%20demolishing%20the%20minaret%20of%20the%20Khajur%20ki%20Masjid.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20ADM%20Amit%20Singh%20said%20the%20demolition%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20being%20rushed%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20mosque%20caretakers%20have%20been%20given%20time%20to%20construct%20a%20supporting%20pillar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20shops%20outside%20the%20mosque%20have%20already%20been%20demolished%20but%20the%20caretaking%20committee%20did%20not%20object%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJournalist%20Husain%20Rizvi%20of%20India%20TV%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Faizabad%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTheHussainRizvi%2Fstatus%2F1675429191448412160%3Ft%3D8bHVaLmTub07SLNoVX2vlg%26s%3D19%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CMany%20temples%20and%20mosques%20have%20been%20removed%20by%20the%20people%20themselves%20for%20the%20Rampath%E2%80%A6The%20administration%20should%20show%20a%20flexible%20approach%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Khajur%20ki%20Masjid.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%2C%20however%2C%20turned%20down%20the%20possibility%20of%20making%20an%20exception%20for%20this%20mosque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdvocate%20Hussain%20also%20asks%20if%20in%20a%20secular%20state%20a%20government%20can%20destroy%20religious%20places%20of%20one%20religion%20to%20make%20way%20for%20pilgrimage%20sites%20of%20another%20religion.%20Many%20Muslims%2C%20a%20local%20said%2C%20have%20complied%20readily%20with%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EActivist%20Azam%20Quadri%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CBabri%20Mosque%20was%20taken%20away%20from%20us%2C%20and%20the%20injustice%20continues%20as%20our%20mosques%20are%20being%20destroyed%20due%20to%20the%20Rampath%20project.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayo