%2Fprisonersofconscience%2Ffatima-al-shawarbi%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESalma%20al-Shehab%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20given%20a%2030-year%20jail%20sentence%20for%20criticizing%20the%20crown%20prince%20on%20the%20social%20media%20platform.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESaudi%20Arabia%20can%20'do%20want%20it%20wants'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Alan%20Woodward%2C%20a%20computer%20technology%20expert%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Surrey%2C%20said%20that%20Saudi%20authorities%20would%20potentially%20be%20able%20to%20access%20vast%20amounts%20of%20sensitive%20political%20information%20stored%20via%20the%20cloud.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20can%20basically%20do%20what%20it%20wants%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you%20can%20imagine%20all%20the%20things%20that%20are%20put%20online%20it%20could%20be%20something%20quite%20edgy%2C%20it%20could%20be%20used%20against%20dissidents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECountries%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20he%20said%2C%20often%20told%20companies%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20you%20want%20to%20operate%20in%20this%20country%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20keep%20the%20data%20in%20this%20country.%20And%20that's%20for%20an%20obvious%20reason%3A%20So%20they%20could%20potentially%20access%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20told%20Insider%20it%20remained%20committed%20to%20human%20rights%2C%20yet%20offered%20no%20concrete%20details%20on%20how%20it%20would%20safeguard%20data%20privacy%20while%20operating%20in%20a%20state%20that%20doesn't%20acknowledge%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRespecting%20human%20rights%20is%20a%20core%20value%20of%20Microsoft.%20Our%20investment%20in%20the%20region%20will%20be%20consistent%20with%20Microsoft's%20commitment%20to%20protecting%20fundamental%20rights%20and%20includes%20a%20focus%20on%20responsible%20cloud%20practices%20including%20security%2C%20privacy%2C%20compliance%2C%20and%20transparency%2C%20as%20well%20as%20adherence%20to%20Microsoft's%20values%20and%20principles%2C%26quot%3B%20a%C2%A0Microsoft%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20spokesperson%20pointed%20Insider%20to%20a%20statement%20on%20the%20company's%20website%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bas%20the%20global%20landscape%20continues%20to%20evolve%2C%20we%20are%20committed%20to%20collaborating%20with%20human%20rights%20organizations%20and%20the%20broader%20technology%20industry%20to%20uphold%20human%20rights%20in%20every%20country%20where%20we%20operate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Lynch%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20human%20rights%20organization%20Fairsquare%2C%20challenged%20Microsoft%20and%20Google%20to%20publish%20their%20human%20rights%20%26quot%3Bdue%20diligence%26quot%3B%20reports%2C%20aimed%20at%20assessing%20how%20they%20can%20ethically%20operate%20in%20a%20country%20with%20a%20poor%20human%20rights%20record.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20said%20the%20companies%20refused%20to%20publish%20the%20reports%20and%20called%20on%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Bshow%20us%20clearly%20how%20they%20plan%20to%20mitigate%20risks%20such%20as%20the%20Saudi%20authorities%20asking%20them%20for%20access%20to%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ENeom%2C%20a%20surveillance%20city%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20particular%20concern%20for%20human%20rights%20activists%20is%20Neom%2C%20the%20vast%20city%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20has%20commissioned%20to%20be%20built%20in%20the%20northeast%20of%20the%20kingdom.%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%20has%20earmarked%20%241%20trillion%20to%20build%20the%20city%2C%20whose%20services%2C%20ranging%20from%20transport%20to%20air%20conditioning%20will%20be%20run%20on%20user%20data%20accessed%20through%20smartphones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsaudi-crown-princes-china-deals-hint-city-darker-neom-mbs-2023-3%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%3EIn%20March%2C%20Insider%20reported%20on%20concerns%20that%20the%20data%20could%20be%20used%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20huge%20surveillance%20systems%20by%20Saudi%20authorities%2C%20to%20track%20and%20monitor%20residents%20in%20real%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20concern%20James%20urged%20Western%20firms%20planning%20on%20being%20involved%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20city's%20digital%20infrastructure%20to%20address.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTying%20in%20almost%20all%20data%20about%20the%20way%20people%20live%20and%20using%20that%20as%20the%20organizing%20principle%20of%20the%20city%20is%20extremely%20scary%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lynch%2C%20in%20a%20country%20with%20at%20best%20opaque%20privacy%20laws%20and%20sweeping%20powers%20to%20suppress%20dissent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20planned%20design%20of%20'The%20Line%2C'%20a%20large%20building%20with%20a%20mirrored%20surface%20that%20extends%20out%20across%20the%20desert%20toward%20the%20coast.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6453a60cb4a8cd00187ab97f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESaudi%20Arabia's%20futuristic%20city%20in%20the%20desert%20hopes%20to%20accommodate%209%20million%20people.%3Cp%3ENEOM%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3ENeither%20Google%20nor%20Microsoft%20would%20say%20whether%20they%20were%20involved%20in%20building%20Neom's%20digital%20infrastructure.%C2%A0%3Cp%3EBut%20amid%20the%20concerns%2C%20there%20is%20also%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20Saudi%20Arabia%20would%20risk%20imperiling%20the%20investment%20it%20has%20pinned%20so%20much%20of%20its%20future%20on%20through%20using%20data%20stored%20in%20the%20kingdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20part%20of%20a%20balancing%20act%20analysts%20have%20told%20Insider%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20has%20long%20sought%20to%20perform%2C%20seeking%20to%20open%20up%20the%20kingdom%20to%20innovation%20and%20appear%20as%20a%20reformer%2C%20while%20maintaining%20his%20authoritarian%20powers%20to%20quash%20dissent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20take%20Neom's%20involvement%20positively%2C%20and%20perhaps%20that%20might%20tip%20one%20over%20into%20sort%20of%20looking%20at%20this%20with%20the%20glass%20half%20full%20and%20say%2C%20'well%2C%20it's%20genuinely%20probably%20part%20of%20the%20kingdom's%20attempts%20to%20diversify%20and%20hence%20have%20more%20technology%20infrastructure%20in%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Woodward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-google-hand-dissident-data-to-saudi-arabia-activists-say-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690195132000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b14b0b9751e300192a1661%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-google-hand-dissident-data-to-saudi-arabia-activists-say-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20seeking%20to%20be%20an%20innovation%20hub%2C%20but%20activists%20are%20warning%20that%20tech%20firms%20could%20be%20complicit%20in%20the%20repression%20of%20dissidents.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-google-hand-dissident-data-to-saudi-arabia-activists-say-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22S%20Club%20to%20Release%20First%20Single%20in%2020%20Years%20%E2%80%93%20Global%20Bulletin%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690194935000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FS-Club.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235678220%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22MUSIC%20S%20Club%2C%20the%20British%20pop%20group%20formerly%20known%20as%20S%20Club%207%2C%20are%20releasing%20a%20new%20single%2C%20%E2%80%9CThese%20Are%20The%20Days%2C%E2%80%9D%20their%20first%20new%20music%20in%2020%20years.%20Performed%20by%20existing%20band%20members%20Tina%20Barrett%2C%20Jon%20Lee%2C%20Bradley%20McIntosh%2C%20Jo%20O%E2%80%99Meara%20and%20Rachel%20Stevens%2C%20the%20song%20is%20by%20the%20songwriting%20team%20of%20Cathy%20Dennis%2C%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fmusic%2Fglobal%2Fs-club-single-1235678220%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fmusic%2Fglobal%2Fs-club-single-1235678220%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Fmusic%2Fglobal%2Fs-club-single-1235678220%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Banks%20Wrote%20off%20Bad%20Loans%20Worth%20Over%20Rs%202%20tn%20in%20FY23%3B%20Rs%2010.57%20tn%20Written%20off%20in%20Last%205%20Years%3A%20RBI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F07182915%2Frbi_pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBanks%20wrote%20off%20bad%20loans%20worth%20over%20Rs%202.09%20lakh%20crore%20(around%20%24%2025.50%20billion)%20during%20the%20year%20ended%20March%202023%2C%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fbanking-and-finance%2Fbanks-write-off-bad-loans-worth-rs-2-09-lakh-crore-in-2022-23-rbi-8856435%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBanks%2520wrote%2520off%2520bad%2520loans%2Cto%2520Information%2520(RTI)%2520reply.%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20reply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20brings%20the%20total%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20the%20banking%20sector%20to%20a%20significant%20Rs%2010.57%20lakh%20crore%20(around%20%24129%20billion)%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20write-offs%20have%20helped%20banks%20to%20bring%20down%20gross%20non-performing%20assets%20(GNPA)%20%E2%80%93%20or%20loans%20defaulted%20by%20borrowers%20%E2%80%93%20to%20a%2010-year%20low%20of%203.9%25%20of%20advances%20in%20March%202023%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGross%20NPAs%20of%20banks%20had%20fallen%20from%20Rs%2010.21%20lakh%20crore%20in%20FY2018%20to%20Rs%205.55%20lakh%20crore%20by%20March%202023%2C%20mainly%20on%20the%20back%20of%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20RBI%20data%2C%20banks%20have%20written%20off%20Rs%2015%2C31%2C453%20crore%20(%24187%20billion)%20since%20FY2012-13.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20loans%20written%20off%20by%20banks%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20books%20of%20banks%20as%20unrecovered%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20reply%20said%20banks%20recovered%20only%20Rs%20109%2C186%20crore%20from%20Rs%20586%2C891%20crore%20loans%20written%20off%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20could%20only%20recover%2018.60%25%20of%20the%20write-offs%20during%20the%20three-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20defaulted%20loans%20(including%20write-offs%20but%20excluding%20loans%20recovered%20from%20write-offs%20in%20three%20years)%20amount%20to%20Rs%2010.32%20lakh%20crore%2C%20the%20daily%20reported%2C%20citing%20the%20back%20of%20the%20envelope%20calculation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20NPA%20ratio%2C%20including%20write-offs%2C%20would%20have%20become%207.47%25%20of%20advances%20as%20against%203.9%25%20reported%20by%20the%20banks%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20fiscal%20ended%20March%202023%2C%20loan%20write-offs%20by%20banks%20rose%20to%20Rs%20209%2C144%20crore%2C%20as%20against%20Rs%20174%2C966%20crore%20a%20year%20ago%20in%20March%202022%2C%20and%20Rs%20202%2C781%20crore%20in%20March%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbysmal%20recoveries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBanks%20write%20off%20loans%20to%20reduce%20NPAs%20in%20their%20books%2C%20however%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20note%20that%20they%20have%20reported%20abysmal%20recoveries%20from%20the%20written%20off%20loans.%20The%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20they%20could%20recover%20only%20Rs%2030%2C104%20crore%20in%20FY21%2C%20Rs%2033%2C534%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20Rs%2045%2C548%20crore%20in%20FY23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20banking%20analyst%20to%20%3Cem%3EIE%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3EAfter%20write-off%2C%20banks%20are%20supposed%20to%20continue%20their%20efforts%20to%20recover%20the%20loan%20using%20various%20options.%20They%20have%20to%20make%20provisioning%20also.%20The%20tax%20liability%20will%20also%20come%20down%20as%20the%20written%20off%20amount%20is%20reduced%20from%20the%20profit.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20loan%20is%20classified%20as%20an%20NPA%20when%20the%20repayment%20of%20the%20principal%20amount%20or%20the%20interest%20remains%20outstanding%20for%20a%20period%20of%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20identity%20of%20these%20borrowers%20was%20never%20revealed%20by%20banks%20or%20the%20RBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20individual%20banks%2C%20reduction%20in%20NPAs%20due%20to%20write-offs%20in%20the%20case%20of%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20was%20Rs%2024%2C061%20crore%20in%20FY2023%2C%20Punjab%20National%20Bank%20Rs%2016%2C578%20crore%2C%20Union%20Bank%20Rs%2019%2C175%20crore%2C%20Central%20Bank%20of%20India%20Rs%2010%2C258%20crore%20and%20Bank%20of%20Baroda%20Rs%2017%2C998%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20substantial%20portion%20of%20this%20write-off%20is%2C%20however%2C%20technical%20in%20nature.%20It%20is%20primarily%20intended%20at%20cleansing%20the%20balance%20sheet%20and%20achieving%20taxation%20efficiency.%20In%20%E2%80%98Technically%20Written%20Off%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98%20accounts%2C%20loans%20are%20written%20off%20from%20the%20books%20at%20the%20Head%20Office%2C%20without%20foregoing%20the%20right%20to%20recovery.%20Further%2C%20write-offs%20are%20generally%20carried%20out%20against%20accumulated%20provisions%20made%20for%20such%20loans.%20Once%20recovered%2C%20the%20provisions%20made%20for%20those%20loans%20flow%20back%20into%20the%20profit%20and%20loss%20account%20of%20banks%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20central%20bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fbanking-and-finance%2Fpsu-banks-write-off-rs-55356-crore-in-six-months-bad-debt-4966594%2F%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20loan%20recovery%20process%20can%20take%20years%20as%20most%20of%20the%20loans%20involved%20in%20write-offs%20belong%20to%20wilful%20defaulters%20and%20promoters%20who%20generally%20don%E2%80%99t%20pay%20back%20to%20the%20banks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20non-transparent%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20without%20any%20policy.%20There%E2%80%99s%20possibility%20of%20wrong-doing.%20Generally%2C%20write-off%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20small%2C%20used%20sparingly%20when%20there%E2%80%99s%20some%20crisis.%20Technical%20write-off%20creates%20non-transparency%2C%20destroys%20the%20credit%20risk%20management%20system%20and%20brings%20all%20types%20of%20wrong-doings%20into%20the%20system.%20You%20must%20declare%20how%20much%20you%E2%80%99re%20writing%20off.%20You%E2%80%99re%20writing%20off%20public%20money.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20scandal.%20You%E2%80%99re%20writing%20off%20public%20money%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20acknowledging%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20RBI%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EIE%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690194622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F07182915%2Frbi_pti.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fbad-loans-npas-written-off-rbi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Banks%20could%20recover%20only%20Rs%2030%2C104%20crore%20in%20FY21%2C%20Rs%2033%2C534%20crore%20in%20FY22%20and%20Rs%2045%2C548%20crore%20in%20FY23%2C%20as%20per%20RBI's%20reply%20to%20the