n%20breaking%20all%20kinds%20of%20international%20laws%2C%20unleashing%20an%20incredibly%20disgusting%20and%20horrific%20level%20of%20destruction%20against%20the%20people%20of%20Ukraine%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReparations%3A%20Another%20path%20to%20peace%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20uncomfortable%20with%20US%20military%20aid%20do%20have%20options%20available%20to%20them%20other%20than%20old-fashioned%20appeasement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewlinesinstitute.org%2Fukraine%2Fmultilateral-framework-for-transferring-state-assets%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20New%20Lines%20Institute%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20based%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20legal%20experts%20argued%20that%20Western%20governments%20should%20immediately%20begin%20using%20frozen%20Russian%20state%20assets%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20reconstruction%20of%20Ukraine's%20oft-targeted%20civilian%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20argument%20is%20that%20Russia%20committed%20the%20supreme%20war%20crime%20of%20an%20unprovoked%20invasion%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20justifies%20countermeasures%20by%20states%20that%20would%20otherwise%20be%20illegal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aim%20is%20not%20just%20to%20make%20the%20perpetrator%20pay%20for%20the%20harm%20already%20inflicted%2C%20a%20demand%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2022%2F11%2F1130587%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eendorsed%20by%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20last%20year%2C%20but%20to%20end%20the%20conflict%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsolidating%20control%20over%20Russian%20assets%20accomplishes%20an%20immediate%20goal%20%E2%80%94%20maximizing%20leverage%2C%20which%20can%20influence%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20write.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20logic%20is%20simple%3A%20The%20more%20money%20Russia%20loses%2C%20the%20more%20interest%20it%20may%20have%20in%20withdrawing%20from%20Ukraine%20without%20first%20demanding%2020%25%20of%20the%20country's%20landmass.%20And%20by%20agreeing%20to%20return%20what's%20left%20of%20the%20reserves%20after%20Russia%20leaves%2C%20another%20financial%20incentive%20is%20provided%20for%20the%20Kremlin%20to%20end%20its%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20military%20operation.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20also%20serves%20a%20policy%20of%20deterrence%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20stated.%20Instead%20of%20showing%20that%20crime%20pays%2C%20as%20would%20a%20territorial%20concession%2C%20%26quot%3BAny%20state%20considering%20a%20future%20war%20of%20aggression%20will%20see%20that%20Russia's%20egregious%20violation%20of%20international%20order%20carries%20a%20cost.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20fringe%20proposal.%20In%20June%2C%20former%20US%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Lawrence%20Summers%2C%20former%20World%20Bank%20President%20Robert%20Zoellick%2C%20and%20former%20US%20diplomat%20Philip%20Zelikow%20co-authored%20an%20endorsement%20of%20the%20reparations%20proposal%2C%20describing%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Fukraine%2Fother-counteroffensive-save-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enonviolent%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20counteroffensive%20that%20might%20also%20please%20a%20domestic%20audience%20worried%20about%20US%20taxpayers%20footing%20the%20bill%20for%20Russian%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTransferring%20frozen%20Russian%20reserves%20to%20Ukraine%20would%20be%20morally%20right%2C%20strategically%20wise%2C%20and%20politically%20expedient%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20Legislation%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreign.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F06-14-23_repo_act.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpressly%20instructing%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20administration%20to%20do%20so%20has%20been%20introduced%20in%20Congress%20with%20bipartisan%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20already%20authorized%20millions%20of%20dollars%20worth%20of%20assets%20from%20Russian%20oligarchs%20to%20be%20transferred%20to%20Ukraine.%20But%20it%20has%20refrained%20from%20touching%20Russia's%20Central%20Bank%20foreign%20currency%20reserves%2C%20which%20are%20estimated%20to%20be%20about%20%2438%20billion%20in%20the%20United%20States%20alone%20(and%20%24215%20billion%20in%20the%20European%20Union).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20on%20whether%20it%20is%20considering%20the%20proposal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Financial%20Times%20economic%20commentator%20Martin%20Sandbu%20wrote%20last%20month%2C%20seizing%20state%20assets%20for%20reparations%20is%20an%20unproven%20legal%20strategy.%20%26quot%3BEven%20so%2C%20politicians%20ostensibly%20determined%20to%20make%20Russia%20pay%20for%20its%20damages%20should%2C%20at%20least%2C%20be%20eager%20to%20explore%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there%20is%20zero%20public%20sign%20that%20anyone%20is%20doing%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20should%20be%20an%20opportunity%20for%20self-styled%20advocates%20of%20peace%20and%20tellers%20of%20hard%20truths.%20If%20the%20United%20States%20and%20others%20are%20actually%20serious%20about%20using%20all%20means%20at%20their%20disposal%20to%20bring%20a%20swift%20end%20to%20this%20war%2C%20why%20aren't%20they%20at%20least%20considering%20%E2%80%94%20as%20far%20as%20we%20know%20%E2%80%94%20this%20more%20palatable%20alternative%20to%20cluster%20munitions%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20don't%20hear%20that.%20When%20given%20a%20microphone%2C%20those%20who%20imagine%20themselves%20the%20true%20heirs%20of%20the%202003%20antiwar%20movement%20instead%20demand%20that%20the%20victim%20of%20an%20unprovoked%20invasion%20first%20be%20disarmed%20and%20then%20forced%20to%20cede%20large%20swaths%20of%20their%20co