is%20no%20feeling%20of%20identity%20to%20the%20whole%20nation%20that%20opposes%20regional%20nationalisms%3F%20To%20discover%20the%20answer%20to%20that%20question%2C%20we%20just%20need%20to%20review%20a%20little%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fifteenth%20century%2C%20the%20Kingdoms%20of%20Aragon%20and%20Castile%20had%20been%20unified%20and%20the%20process%20of%20expansion%20to%20America%2C%20led%20by%20the%20Crown%20of%20Castile%2C%20had%20begun.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20we%20can%20only%20identify%20a%20certain%20%E2%80%9Cpre-national%E2%80%9D%20identity%20that%20is%20more%20related%20to%20loyalty%20to%20the%20Spanish%20Monarchy%20and%20to%20the%20Spanish%20Empire%20than%20to%20a%20line%20of%20thought%20having%20to%20do%20with%20a%20national%20concept%20of%20Spain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20did%20the%20idea%20of%20Spain%20as%20a%20single%20nation%20arise%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20in%20the%20nineteenth%20century%20when%20a%20school%20of%20thought%20that%20promoted%20the%20unity%20and%20identity%20of%20Spain%20as%20a%20single%20and%20indivisible%20nation%20really%20emerged.%20This%20came%20about%20in%20a%20context%20of%20social%20unrest%20after%20the%20domestic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPeninsular_War%5C%22%3EPeninsular%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20traumatic%20loss%20of%20the%20American%20colonies.%20It%20was%20put%20forward%20by%20figures%20such%20as%20Spanish%20politicians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FAntonio_C%25C3%25A1novas_del_Castillo%5C%22%3EAntonio%20C%C3%A1novas%20del%20Castillo%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FJuan_Donoso_Cort%25C3%25A9s%5C%22%3EJuan%20Donoso%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIdeas%20of%20centralism%20and%20the%20territorial%20unity%20of%20Spain%20were%20a%20significant%20part%20of%20this%20ideology.%20Patriotism%20and%20the%20defence%20of%20the%20nation%20were%20also%20central%2C%20as%20was%20Catholicism%20and%20traditionalism%2C%20reinforced%20by%20an%20opposition%20to%20more%20liberal%20currents%20that%20promoted%20the%20modernisation%20of%20Spain.%20These%20were%20perceived%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20Spanish%20identity%20and%20traditionalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20feeling%20of%20Spanish%20identity%20was%20reinforced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe-revistas.uc3m.es%2Findex.php%2Fhispnov%2Farticle%2Fview%2F1874%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20Franco%20dictatorship%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%201939-1975.%20Francoism%20used%20the%20ideological%20concepts%20of%20Spanish%20nationalism%20to%20justify%20its%20authoritarian%20and%20centralist%20regime%2C%20as%20well%20as%20harsh%20repression%20against%20any%20form%20of%20political%20dissent%20or%20claim%20for%20regional%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20was%20to%20be%20expected%2C%20during%20the%20transition%20to%20democracy%20(1976-1982)%2C%20there%20was%20a%20strong%20resurgence%20of%20regional%20identity%20in%20Catalonia%20and%20the%20Basque%20Country.%20This%20demanded%20greater%20amounts%20of%20autonomy%20and%20self-government.%20In%20opposition%20to%20this%2C%20there%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20significant%20reaction%20by%20Spanish%20nationalism%2C%20which%20had%20been%20weakened%20by%20its%20ideological%20proximity%20to%20Franco%E2%80%99s%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20consolidation%20of%20democracy%20and%20the%20overcoming%20of%20the%20Franco%20dictatorship%20%E2%80%93%20starting%20in%20the%201980s%20%E2%80%93%20entailed%20the%20strengthening%20of%20new%20political%20currents.%20These%20began%20to%20claim%20the%20national%20identity%20and%20territorial%20unity%20of%20Spain%20more%20vehemently%2C%20doing%20so%20in%20opposition%20to%20the%20peripheral%20nationalist%20movements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20nationalist%20sentiment%20always%20right%20wing%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20political%20parties%20that%20defend%20Spanish%20nationalism%20with%20great%20intensity%20is%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20of%20Jose%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Aznar%2C%20as%20well%20as%20several%20extreme%20right-wing%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20is%20important%20to%20point%20out%20that%20Spanish%20nationalism%20is%20not%20an%20exclusive%20phenomenon%20of%20the%20political%20right.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fletraslibres.com%2Fpolitica%2Fizquierda-y-nacionalismo-teoria-historia-y-estrategia%2F%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20nationalist%20lines%20of%20thought%20on%20the%20left%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20also%20defend%20the%20identity%20and%20unity%20of%20Spain.%20However%2C%20they%20do%20it%20from%20a%20broader%20perspective%20of%20dialogue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAznar%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20(1996-2004)%20was%20characterised%20by%20placing%20Spanish%20nationalism%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20political%20scene.%20His%20government%20implemented%20initiatives%20that%20entailed%20a%20substantial%20change%20in%20the%20Spanish%20political%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20most%20noteworthy%20is%20the%20breaking%2C%20by%20the%20Spanish%20government%2C%20of%20the%20balance%20established%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapp.congreso.es%2Fconsti%2Fconstitucion%2Findice%2Ftitulos%2Farticulos.jsp%3Fini%3D137%26fin%3D158%26tipo%3D2%5C%22%3ETitle%20VIII%20of%20the%20Constitution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20set%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapp.congreso.es%2Fconsti%2Fconstitucion%2Findice%2Fsinopsis%2Fsinopsis.jsp%3Fart%3D151%26tipo%3D2%5C%22%3Edifferent%20levels%20of%20competence%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cnbetween%20historical%20autonomous%20communities%20(Catalonia%2C%20Galicia%20and%20the%20Basque%20Country)%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapp.congreso.es%2Fconsti%2Fconstitucion%2Findice%2Ftitulos%2Farticulos.jsp%3Fini%3D143%26tipo%3D2%5C%22%3Ethe%20rest%20of%20the%20Spanish%20autonomous%20communities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Constitution%20of%201978%20differentiated%20between%20those%20communities%20that%20had%20a%20statute%20of%20autonomy%20prior%20to%20the%20Spanish%20Civil%20War%20and%20those%20that%20did%20not.%20And%20gave%20these%20three%20more%20power%20to%20decide%20over%20their%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20application%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapp.congreso.es%2Fconsti%2Fconstitucion%2Findice%2Ftitulos%2Farticulos.jsp%3Fini%3D152%26tipo%3D2%5C%22%3Earticle%20152%3C%2Fa%3E%20culminated%20in%20a%20policy%20of%20transfer%20of%20power%20that%20practically%20equated%20the%20competences%20of%20all%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20some%20other%20political%20initiatives%20have%20brought%20about%20a%20feeling%20of%20unfair%20treatment%20and%20contributed%20to%20a%20spiral%20of%20demands%20by%20the%20Catalan%20and%20Basque%20governments%2C%20which%20wish%20to%20maintain%20special%20status%20within%20the%20Spanish%20autonomous%20framework.%20These%20initiatives%20include%20the%20consolidation%20of%20a%20Spain%20that%20spreads%20in%20a%20radial%20manner%20out%20from%20Madrid%2C%20the%20tax%20policy%20of%20the%20Community%20of%20Madrid%20%E2%80%93%20more%20lax%20than%20in%20other%20communities%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20investments%20in%20the%20Mediterranean%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20starting%20in%202010%20and%20coinciding%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fes.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FSentencia_del_Tribunal_Constitucional_sobre_el_Estatuto_de_Autonom%25C3%25ADa_de_Catalu%25C3%25B1a_de_2006%5C%22%3EConstitutional%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20on%20the%20Catalan%20Statute%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20very%20turbulent%20stage%20of%20Spanish%20politics%20began%2C%20characterised%20by%20strong%20political%20confrontation%20between%20the%20various%20nationalisms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20feeling%20of%20identity%20of%20recent%20years%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D2RdsKh0N9Rc%5C%22%3EThe%20%E2%80%9CProc%C3%A8s%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Catalan%20Process%20for%20Sovereignty%3B%202010-2017)%20became%20a%20spiral%20of%20confrontation%20between%20Catalan%20nationalism%20and%20Spanish%20nationalism.%20The%20first%20one%20wanted%20to%20be%20recognised%20as%20a%20political%20player%20with%20the%20right%20to%20self-determination.%20Whereas%20the%20second%20one%20denied%20any%20possibility%20of%20negotiation%2C%20using%20all%20the%20State%E2%80%99s%20mechanisms%20available%20to%20prevent%20the%20referendum%20being%20held%20on%20October%201%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20within%20this%20context%20of%20%E2%80%9Cresponse%20to%20the%20Catalan%20independence%20movement%E2%80%9D%20that%20we%20must%20note%20the%20significant%20growth%20of%20a%20feeling%20of%20Spanish%20identity%20in%20recent%20years.%20The%20implementation%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Spain%E2%80%99s%20right-wing%20conservative%2C%20liberal%2C%20and%20radical%20parties%20(PP%2C%20Cs%2C%20and%20Vox)%20%E2%80%93%20of%20policies%20and%20campaigns%20aimed%20at%20confrontation%20with%20peripheral%20nationalisms%20were%20also%20born%20after%20that%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20intend%20to%20reinforce%20the%20principles%20of%20centralisation%2C%20national%20identity%2C%20and%20territorial%20unity%20%E2%80%93%20principles%20so%20typical%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faragondigital.es%2Fpolitica%2F2019%2F11%2F03%2Fvox-considera-a-aragon-un-muro-de-contencion-de-los-nacionalismos-vasco-y-catalan%2F%5C%22%3ESpain%E2%80%99s%20sense%20of%20identity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F209052%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EV%C3%ADctor%20Climent%20Sanju%C3%A1n%20is%20Profesor%20Titular%20de%20Sociolog%C3%ADa%2C%20Universitat%20de%20Barcelona.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthecon