m%2Fcovid-19-pandemic-ended-normal-work-week-9-5-workday-2020-7%5C%22%3Estandard%209-to-5%20workday%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20many%20in%20the%20US.%20Say%20hello%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-jobs-schedule-errands-leisure-during-work-hours-2023-3%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Btriple%20peak%26quot%3B%20workday%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-changed-economy-pandemic-2023-4%5C%22%3Eits%20effects%20on%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20reconfigured%20the%20white-collar%20employee's%20workday%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20including%20by%20changing%20what%20time%20of%20day%20they're%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagers%20are%20reporting%20a%20%26quot%3Bdead%20zone%26quot%3B%20from%204%20pm%20to%206%20pm%2C%20when%20workers%20are%20signing%20off%20early%20before%20logging%20on%20again%20later%20to%20wrap%20up%20their%20work%20for%20the%20day%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fwork-office-coworkers-schedule-meetings-2af3f9b0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20reported.%20Workers%20are%20using%20the%20time%20to%20run%20errands%2C%20pick%20up%20their%20kids%2C%20commute%20home%20before%20rush%20hour%2C%20or%20use%20the%20time%20for%20leisurely%20purposes%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnbloom.people.stanford.edu%2Fsites%2Fg%2Ffiles%2Fsbiybj24291%2Ffiles%2Fmedia%2Ffile%2Fgolfingfromhome.pdf%5C%22%3Ehitting%20the%20golf%20course%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Btriple%20peak%26quot%3B%20day%2C%20as%20The%20Atlantic's%20Derek%20Thompson%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Fnewsletters%2Farchive%2F2022%2F04%2Ftriple-peak-day-work-from-home%2F629457%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20April.%20In%20a%20study%20that%20year%2C%20Microsoft%20researchers%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D569a91d5c4ba5f6d5b2eddff0807736f219e5a1866d33f114dc02ba33753c1fa%26postID%3D64ba8eaa818c7a7ff1df4709%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.microsoft.com%252Fen-us%252Fworklab%252Ftriple-peak-day%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20their%20employees%20previously%20exhibited%20two%20productivity%20peaks%20in%20a%20day%2C%20as%20measured%20by%20keyboard%20activity%2C%20one%20around%2011%20am%20and%20the%20other%20around%203%20pm.%20But%20roughly%2030%25%20of%20Microsoft%20employees%20in%20the%20study%20now%20had%20a%20third%20productivity%20peak%20in%20the%20day%2C%20around%2010%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shifting%20schedule%20can%20have%20positive%20and%20negative%20consequences%20for%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20imagine%20the%20effect%20on%20collaboration%20if%20your%20colleagues%20need%20something%20from%20you%2C%20but%20you%20won't%20be%20back%20on%20until%20after%20they've%20all%20logged%20off%20for%20the%20day.%20As%20Colette%20Stallbaumer%2C%20general%20manager%20of%20Microsoft's%20Future%20of%20Work%20initiative%2C%20told%20the%20Journal%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20make%20it%20so%20that%20my%20flexibility%20isn't%20your%20challenge%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20those%20whose%20work%20is%20more%20solitary%20or%20not%20as%20time-sensitive%2C%20the%20triple%20peak%20day%20may%20offer%20a%20pathway%20to%20greater%20work-life%20balance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-are-quitting-struggling-at-work-because-of-childcare-crisis-2023-6%5C%22%3EWorking%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20might%20adopt%20a%20triple%20peak%20day%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20their%20kids%20during%20the%20day%20and%20finish%20work%20once%20their%20kids%20are%20off%20to%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20schedule%20could%20further%20blur%20the%20lines%20between%20your%20home%20life%20and%20work%20if%20you%20end%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-time-saved-from-commuting-study-2023-1%5C%22%3Eworking%20longer%20than%20you%20would%20have%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20your%20standard%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20single%20person%20on%20a%20team%20has%20a%20different%20context%20within%20which%20they're%20trying%20to%20be%20productive%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D569a91d5c4ba5f6d5b2eddff0807736f219e5a1866d33f114dc02ba33753c1fa%26postID%3D64ba8eaa818c7a7ff1df4709%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.microsoft.com%252Fen-us%252Fworklab%252Ftriple-peak-day%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20Mary%20Czerwinski%2C%20a%20research%20manager%20at%20Microsoft%20who%20worked%20on%20the%20triple%20peak%20day%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20give%20everyone%20space%20to%20do%20it%20on%20their%20terms.%20Some%20of%20them%20might%20have%20babies%2C%20some%20of%20them%20have%20teenagers%2C%20some%20of%20them%20might%20not%20have%20kids%2C%20but%20they%20work%20best%20at%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSome%20are%20in%20another%20time%20zone%20and%20are%20asynchronous.%20The%20key%20is%2C%20they%20can%20all%20be%20productive%2C%20but%20they%20have%20to%20do%20it%20in%20a%20way%20and%20at%20a%20time%20that's%20personalized.%20It's%20all%20over%20the%20place%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20you%20can%20be%20your%20original%20self%20at%20work%20and%20really%20contribute.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20working%20a%20%26quot%3Btriple%20peak%26quot%3B%20day%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Asjackson%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esjackson%40insider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%