plaint%20against%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efatwas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20issued%20by%20Darul%20Uloom%20Deoband.%20The%20fatwa%20references%20a%20book%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBahishti%20Zewar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20book%20contains%20content%20regarding%20children%20that%20is%20objectionable%2C%20improper%20and%20illegal%20and%20the%20book%20is%20also%20alleged%20to%20be%20taught%20to%20children%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Emadrasas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fnational%2Fnorth-and-central%2Fncpcr-seeks-action-against-darul-uloom-deobands-book-legitimising-sex-with-minors-1239954.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20district%20commission%20and%20senior%20superintendent%20of%20police%2C%20Saharanpur%20on%20July%2014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fnational%2Fnorth-and-central%2Fncpcr-seeks-action-against-darul-uloom-deobands-book-legitimising-sex-with-minors-1239954.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20material%20should%20be%20blocked%20under%20section%2069A%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%20which%20allows%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20ask%20any%20of%20its%20agencies%20or%20an%20intermediary%20to%20block%20public%20access%20to%20any%20information%20generated%20stored%20on%20any%20computer%20resource.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20child%20rights%20body%20has%20asked%20for%20a%20copy%20of%20all%20the%20books%20prescribed%20in%20the%20syllabus%20and%20an%20%E2%80%98action%20taken%E2%80%99%20report%20from%20the%20district%20administration%20in%20four%20days.%20This%20is%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20second%20complaint%20since%20January%20last%20year%20when%20it%20had%20written%20to%20the%20administration%20about%20the%20presence%20of%20several%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efatwas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20Darul%20Uloom%E2%80%99s%20website%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENCPCR%20chief%20Priyank%20Kanoongo%20said%20that%20the%20book%20legitimises%20sexual%20relations%20with%20minors.%20%E2%80%9CBy%20minors%2C%20we%20mean%20girls%20who%20are%20yet%20to%20reach%20puberty.%20There%20are%20passages%20that%20say%20that%20men%20do%20not%20have%20to%20bathe%20after%20such%20an%20act%20to%20read%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Enamaz%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20There%20are%20several%20such%20references%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kanungo%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInterestingly%2C%20a%20chapter%20in%20the%20NCERT-prescribed%20English%20textbook%20for%20Class%2011th%20on%20child%20marriage%20and%20sexual%20relations%20with%20a%20minor%20has%20gone%20under%20the%20NCPCR%E2%80%99s%20radar.%20The%20chapter%2C%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERanga%E2%80%99s%20Marriage%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20about%20a%20man%20in%20his%20mid-twenties%20who%20marries%20an%2011-year-old%20and%20has%20two%20children%20with%20her%20before%20she%20turns%2015.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20opposition%20leader%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20has%20criticised%20the%20NCPCR%20for%20pushing%20a%20soft%20Hindutva%20agenda%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20%3Cem%3EThePrint%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fground-reports%2Fncpcr-has-a-new-mojo-and-mission-aap-madrasas-byjus-nothing-is-off-limits%2F1647621%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Kanoongo%20has%20also%20been%20called%20out%20for%20turning%20the%20NCPCR%E2%80%99s%20focus%20away%20from%20ensuring%20child%20rights%20and%20meddling%20in%20political%20warfare%20that%20is%20outside%20the%20commission%E2%80%99s%20purview.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690183363000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F24124346%2FDarul_Uloom_Deoband.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fncpcr-seeks-removal-of-controversial-book-from-darul-uloom-deobands-curriculum%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20child%20rights%20body%20has%20said%20that%20Maulana%20Ashraf%20Ali%20Thanvi's%20book%C2%A0Bahishti%20Zewar%C2%A0legitimises%20sexual%20relations%20with%20minors%20and%20should%20be%20blocked%20under%20section%2069A%20of%20the%20IT%20Act.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fncpcr-seeks-removal-of-controversial-book-from-darul-uloom-deobands-curriculum%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Key%20Bills%20Expected%20To%20Be%20Tabled%20In%20Parliament%20Today%20And%20Their%20Significance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20monsoon%20session%2C%20Parliament%20has%20seen%20some%20angry%20scenes%20and%20walkouts%20from%20opposition%20parties%2C%20which%20has%20led%20to%20multiple%20disruptions%20in%20both%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20On%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20Parliament%20session%2C%20Union%20minister%20Pralhad%20Joshi%20had%20said%20that%2031%20bills%20will%20be%20taken%20up%20but%20so%20far%2C%20the%20legislative%20business%20has%20been%20impacted%20by%20the%20protests.%20On%20Monday%20(July%2024)%2C%20these%20important%20bills%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20tabled%20in%20Parliament%20if%20it%20functions.%20Here's%20a%20look%20at%20them%20and%20the%20significance%20they%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20bills%20likely%20to%20be%20taken%20up%20for%20consideration%20and%20passing%20is%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Multi-State%20Co-operative%20Societies%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20It%20will%20be%20tabled%20by%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20seeks%20to%20amend%20the%20Multi-State%20Co-operative%20Societies%20Act%2C%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20MSCS%20(Amendment)%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20December%207%20last%20year.%20It%20was%20referred%20to%20a%20Joint%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20of%20both%20the%20Houses%20on%20December%2020%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Centre%2C%20the%20bill%20will%20strengthen%20accountability%20in%20cooperative%20societies%20and%20reform%20their%20electoral%20process%20by%20improving%20the%20monitoring%20mechanism%20and%20ease%20of%20doing%20business%20in%20state%20cooperatives.%20The%20bill%20will%20also%20allow%20state%20cooperative%20societies%20to%20merge%20into%20an%20existing%20multi-state%20cooperative%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20important%20provisions%20entails%20that%20a%20prior%20government%20permission%20will%20be%20required%20for%20multi-state%20co-operative%20societies%20for%20the%20redemption%20of%20their%20shareholding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20opposition%20parties%20are%20opposed%20to%20it%20saying%20they%20won't%20allow%20central%20interference%20in%20the%20working%20of%20cooperatives%20as%20it%20is%20a%20state%20subject%20and%20many%20of%20the%20bill's%20provisions%20go%20against%20the%20autonomy%20enjoyed%20by%20these%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20important%20bill%20expected%20to%20be%20tabled%20is%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Biological%20Diversity%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20It%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20discussed%20during%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20the%20budget%20session%20but%20was%20deferred.%20The%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20Parliament%20on%20December%2016%2C%202021%20by%20Bhupender%20Yadav%2C%20Union%20minister%20for%20environment%2C%20forest%20and%20climate%20change%20and%20seeks%20to%20amend%20the%20Biological%20Diversity%20Act%2C%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20legislation%20seeks%20to%20reduce%20the%20burden%20on%20wild%20medicinal%20plants%20and%20encourage%20their%20cultivation.%20It%20is%20aimed%20at%20encouraging%20Indian%20system%20of%20medicine%20and%20facilitate%20an%20environment%20for%20collaborative%20research%20and%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20also%20seeks%20to%20exempt%20those%20making%20medicinal%20products%20from%20taking%20permission%20from%20the%20National%20Biodiversity%20Authority%20(NBA)%20and%20decriminalise%20violation%20and%20withdraw%20power%20given%20to%20it%20to%20file%20an%20FIR%20against%20a%20defaulting%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20was%20moved%20to%20a%20joint%20committee%20on%20December%2020%2C%202021%20due%20to%20concerns%20that%20the%20amendments%20contradicted%20the%20spirit%20of%20Convention%20on%20Biological%20Diversity%20(CBD).%20%C2%A0The%20panel%20submitted%20its%20report%20in%20Parliament%20on%20August%202%2C%202022%2C%20recommending%20that%20the%20bill%20may%20be%20passed%20after%20the%20inclusion%20of%20their%20suggestions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20has%20rejected%20the%20amendments%20saying%20it%20favours%20trade%20and%20business%20over%20conservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20important%20bill%20ready%20for%20consideration%20is%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20National%20Nursing%20and%20Midwifery%20Commission%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20It%20seeks%20to%20a%20new%20commission%20that%20will%20frame%20policies%2C%20regulate%20standards%20of%20nursing%20and%20midwifery%20education%20and%20frame%20regulation%20for%20their%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20proposes%20to%20provide%20uniform%20entry%20and%20exit%20examinations%2C%20monitor%20professional%20ethics%20and%20control%20state%20commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20bill%2C%20the%20members%20of%20the%20commission%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20central%20and%20state%20ministries%2C%20and%20a%20meeting%20will%20be%20held%20at%20least%20once%20every%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Constitution%20(Scheduled%20Castes)%20Order%20(Amendment)%20Bill%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20be%20tabled%20today%20by%20Minister%20of%20Tribal%20Affairs%20Arjun%20Munda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%2C%20already%20passed%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20talks%20about%20including%20certain%20communities%20in%20Chhattisgarh%20in%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20list.%20The%20minister%20could%20also%20move%20the%20%3Cstrong%3EConstitution%20(Scheduled%20Tribes)%20Order%20(Third%20Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20on%20the%20ST%20list%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690182840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-07%2Frtvrrj68_parliament-generic-pti_625x300_23_July_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkey-bills-expected-to-be-tabled-in-parliament-today-and-their-significance-4235679%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20monsoon%20session%2C%20Union%20minister%20Pralhad%20Joshi%20had%20said%20that%2031%20bills%20will%20be%20taken%20up%20by%20Parliament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkey-bills-expected-to-be-tabled-in-parliament-today-and-their-significance-4235679%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkey-bills-expected-to-be-tabled-in-parliament-today-and-their-significance-4235679%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkey-bills-expected-to-be-tabled-in-parliament-today-and-their-significance-4235679%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Raigad%3A%20Dozens%20still%20missing%20as%20India%20landslide%20search%20called%20off%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690182826000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1FFD%2Fproduction%2F_130498180_raigad.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-india-66287