20in%20the%20early%201960s%2C%20the%20Indian%20film%20industry%20was%20dominated%20by%20Hindi-language%20movies%2C%20thus%20providing%20little%20to%20no%20opportunity%20for%20regional%20script%20movies.%20This%20spell%20ended%20in%201963%20with%20Kundan%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20Bhojpuri%20film%20%3Cem%3EGanga%20Maiya%20Tohe%20Piyari%20Chadhaibo%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20poignant%20film%20on%20widow%20remarriage.%20In%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20a%20young%20film%20enthusiast%20Manu%20Nayak%20was%20so%20influenced%20by%20this%20that%20it%20compelled%20him%20to%20make%20a%20Chhattisgarhi%20film%20on%20a%20subject%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2Fweb-stories%2Flawyer-dedicated-two-decades-to-helping-inter-caste-couples-love-freely-live-safely%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20was%20passionate%20about%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20353px)%20100vw%2C%20353px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-3-1689943324.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22353%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kahi%20Debe%20Sandesh%20faced%20major%20backlash%20following%20its%20release%20for%20shedding%20light%20on%20caste%20discrimination%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-3-1689943324.jpg%20353w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-3-1689943324-300x233.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-3-1689943324-150x116.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-324748%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKahi%20Debe%20Sandesh%20faced%20major%20backlash%20following%20its%20release%20for%20shedding%20light%20on%20caste%20discrimination%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20A%20photobook%20by%20Aayush%20Chandrawanshi%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDirected%20by%20Nayak%20and%20released%20in%201965%2C%20%3Cem%3EKahi%20Debe%20Sandesh%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20talk%20of%20the%20town%20for%20more%20reasons%20than%20one.%20Not%20only%20was%20the%20film%E2%80%99s%20plot%20considered%20controversial%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20the%20first%20film%20in%20the%20Chhattisgarhi%20language%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20film%20industry%20was%20dominated%20by%20Hindi%20films.%20It%20must%20also%20be%20remembered%20that%20this%20event%20was%20much%20before%20Chhattisgarh%20came%20into%20existence%20as%20a%20state%20in%202000.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20detailed%20the%20love%20story%20of%20Nayandas%20and%20Rupa%2C%20a%20boy%20from%20a%20scheduled%20caste%20and%20a%20Brahmin%20girl%20respectively.%20The%20storyline%20faced%20the%20ire%20of%20conservatives%20and%20leaders%20across%20the%20nation%2C%20notably%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F177183%2Fbihar-hero-fight-untouchability-caste-system-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrahmin%20community%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Raipur.%20Nayak%20recalled%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20a%20sudden%20there%20was%20a%20controversy%2C%20where%20a%20section%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20community%20accused%20the%20film%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20disrespects%20their%20community.%20They%20protested%20the%20release%20of%20the%20film%20in%20Raipur%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20these%20groups%20forced%20posters%20of%20the%20movie%20to%20be%20taken%20down%2C%20many%20prominent%20voices%20spoke%20up%20against%20this.%20One%20of%20them%20was%20former%20prime%20minister%20Indira%20Gandhi.%20Nayak%20later%20recalled%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20help%20came%20from%20two%20%E2%80%9Cprogressive%E2%80%9D%20politicians.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20told%20Indira%20Gandhi%20(then%20I%26amp%3BB%20Minister)%20also%20saw%20portions%20of%20the%20film%20and%20said%20the%20film%20promotes%20national%20integration.%20The%20protests%20died%20down%20after%20that.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20crew%20powered%20through%20the%20backlash%20and%20managed%20to%20have%20the%20film%20premiere%20in%20April%201965.%20Ironically%2C%20the%20hullabaloo%20that%20the%20film%20created%20drew%20more%20attention%20with%20people%20flocking%20to%20cinema%20screens%20to%20catch%20it.%20It%20opened%20the%20windows%20for%20society%20to%20take%20cognisance%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F23061%2Fone-man-is-breaking-all-stereotypes-attached-with-indian-weddings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevils%20of%20the%20caste%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20film%20also%20served%20as%20the%20launchpad%20for%20Chhollywood%20(as%20the%20film%20industry%20of%20Chhattisgarh%20is%20popularly%20known)%20and%20was%20screened%20in%20Raipur%20in%202015%20at%20a%20film%20festival%20to%20mark%20the%20jubilee%20of%20this%20event.%20For%20Nayak%2C%20this%20event%20held%20tremendous%20significance.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20196px)%20100vw%2C%20196px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-4-1689943596.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22196%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22While%20members%20of%20the%20Brahmin%20community%20in%20Raipur%20threatened%20to%20ban%20the%20film%2C%20it%20was%20applauded%20by%20many%20important%20figures%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-4-1689943596.jpg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-4-1689943596-127x300.jpg%20127w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FManu-4-1689943596-150x354.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20cla